[few_shot][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 77/100 done id=gsm8k_test_946 prediction='First, we calculate how many loaves of bread the bakery has based on what Sam originally had. Since the bakery has 40 less than seven times as many loaves of bread as Sam had last Friday, we can set up the equation:\n\n\\[ \\text{Number of loaves} = 7 \\times (\\text{Number of loaves Sam had}) - 40 \\]\n\nGiven that Sam had 70 loaves of bread last Friday, we substitute this value into the equation:\n\n\\[ \\text{Number of loaves} = 7 \\times (70) - 40 \\]\n\\[ \\text{Number of loaves} = 490 - 40 \\]\n\\[ \\text{Number of loaves} = 450 \\]\n\nSo, the bakery has 450 loaves of bread.' gold='450' correct=False
