[few_shot][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][mmlu] sample 25/100 done id=mmlu_test_3150 prediction='To find the pKa of the weak acid, we need to follow these steps:\n\n1. **Calculate the concentration of the weak acid**: \n   - We know the volume of the solution (0.25 L) and the moles of the weak acid (0.25 mol).\n   - The concentration \\( [HA] \\) can be calculated using the formula: \n     \\[\n     [HA] = \\frac{\\text{moles of HA}}{\\text{volume of solution}}\n     \\]\n   - Substituting the given values:\n     \\[\n     [HA] = \\frac{0.25 \\text{ mol}}{0.25 \\text{ L}} = 1 \\text{ M}\n     \\]\n\n2. **Use the Henderson-Hasselbalch equation**:\n   - The pKa is defined as the negative logarithm of the ratio of the concentrations of the conjugate base (bromide ion, \\( [B^-] \\)) to the acid (acetic acid, \\( [HA] \\)):\n     \\[\n     \\text{p}K_a = -\\log\\left(\\frac{[B^-]}{[HA]}\\right)\n     \\]\n   - Given' gold='B' correct=False
