[few_shot][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][mmlu] sample 8/100 done id=mmlu_test_1139 prediction='Use the subject knowledge to analyze each statement:\n\nI. The trace of A^2 is nonnegative.\n- This is true because the trace of a matrix is the sum of its eigenvalues, and the square of a number (the eigenvalue squared) is always nonnegative.\n\nII. If A^2 = A, then the trace of A is nonnegative.\n- This is false. Consider a diagonal matrix where one entry is negative. For example, let \\( A = \\begin{pmatrix} -1 & 0 \\\\ 0 & 0 \\end{pmatrix} \\). Then \\( A^2 = (-1)^2 \\cdot I = I \\), but the trace of \\( A \\) is -1, which is negative.\n\nIII. The trace of AB is the product of the traces of A and B.\n- This is false. The trace of the product of two matrices does not equal the product of their traces. There is no general formula relating the trace of the product to the traces of the individual matrices.\n\nFinal Answer: D. II and III only' gold='A' correct=False
