[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 30/100 path 1/3 answer="To find out how many steps Elliott took during his jog, let's break down the information given:\n\n1. Elliott walked half of his total steps to and from school.\n   - Steps taken to school = Steps taken from school / 2\n   - Steps taken from school = Total steps / 2\n\n2. Elliott then walked an additional 1,000 steps going for a short walk with his friend.\n\n3. After jogging around the block, he had 2,000 steps left to take.\n\nLet's calculate the number of steps taken during his jog:\n\n- Steps taken to school = (Total steps) / 2\n- Steps taken walking with friends = 1,000\n- Steps remaining after jogging = 2,000\n\nSince we know the total steps are 10,000:\nSteps taken to school = 5,000\nSteps taken walking with friends = 1,000\n\nNow, subtract these two amounts from the total steps:\nRemaining steps after jogging = 10,000 - 5,000 - 1,000 = 4,000\n\nTherefore, Elliott took 4,000 steps during his jog."
