[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 43/100 path 1/3 answer='To determine how many popsicle sticks Frederick can make with the available budget, we need to calculate the cost per stick for each type of wood and then find out how many of each type he can afford based on his total budget.\n\n1. Calculate the cost per stick for the 2x4 piece of wood:\n   \\[\n   \\text{Cost per stick} = \\frac{\\$4}{\\text{Number of sticks}} = \\frac{\\$4}{200}\n   \\]\n\n2. Calculate the cost per stick for the 2x8 piece of wood:\n   \\[\n   \\text{Cost per stick} = \\frac{\\$6}{\\text{Number of sticks}} = \\frac{\\$6}{400}\n   \\]\n\n3. Determine which type of wood allows him to spend as much as his budget without exceeding it:\n\n   - For the 2x4 piece of wood:\n     \\[\n     \\left(\\frac{\\$4}{200}\\right) + (24 - 4) = \\left(\\frac{\\$4}{200}\\right) + \\$20\n     \\]\n     Since \\(24 > 20\\), the 2x4 piece of wood will allow him to buy more than 200 sticks.\n\n   - For the 2x8 piece of wood:\n     \\[\n     \\left(\\frac{\\$6}{400}\\right) + (24 - 4) = \\left(\\frac{\\$6}{400}\\right) + \\$20\n     \\]\n     Since \\(24 > 20\\), the 2x8 piece of wood will allow him to buy more than 200 sticks.\n\nSince buying both types would exceed his budget, he should choose the cheaper option first.\n\n4. Compare'
