[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 74/100 path 1/3 answer="To find the average number of Junebugs removed per day, we first need to calculate the total number of Junebugs removed over the week.\n\nOn Monday, Rita removed 39 bugs.\nOn Tuesday and Wednesday, she removed twice as many as Monday, which is \\(2 \\times 39 = 78\\) bugs each day.\nOn Thursday, she removed 48 bugs.\nOn Friday, she removed 57 bugs.\n\nThe total number of bugs removed can then be calculated as:\n\\[39 + 78 + 78 + 48 + 57\\]\n\nNow let's calculate the sum.\nSumming up all the numbers gives us the total number of bugs:\n\\[39 + 78 + 78 + 48 + 57 = 301\\]\n\nThere are 5 days (Monday through Friday) so, the average number of bugs removed per day would be the total number divided by the number of days:\n\\[ \\frac{301}{5} = 60.2\\]\n\nTherefore, the average number of Junebugs that Rita removes per day is **60.2**."
