[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][mmlu] sample 98/100 path 1/3 answer='American exceptionalism, often associated with President Theodore Roosevelt\'s advocacy for "No Man\'s Land," suggests an emphasis on individualism and self-reliance rather than collective action or international cooperation (Option A). It also implies that U.S. economic policies should focus more on domestic issues to maintain balance (Option C).\n\nThe concept of American exceptionalism emphasizes the superiority of American culture, institutions, and values compared to other nations. This view might encourage unilateral actions without consulting others (Option D), leading to potential misallocation of resources and economic disparities.\n\nTherefore, the correct answer is Option B, as it directly reflects American exceptionalism’s impact on global economics through encouragement of nationalization and interventionist policies (Option B).'
